Bxf7 is the best 7th move here for white, taking away blacks castling rights.
black moves his king out of check.
The move 8.Be6+ forks blacks king and Knight putting black into check again.

Black moves his king to c6. From what I've read this is the more popular move for black, I am not quite sure why but I am thinking 8.Kc7 is not a good move because of a possible check threat from whites knight on g5, I could be wrong and would love to hear some feedback.
Capturing blacks knight.
Again 9.e6 is the most favored move for black from what I have read but not quite sure why, any comments is much appreciated.

I am not sure whether this was a good move or a bad move, the reason for why I moved it was because of black moving 10.h6 and attacking my knight and therefore I would have to move the knight anyway. But I feel there could of been a better 10th move here.
Expected.
11.Nf2 Blocking the check from blacks queen. I feel this could be a bad move and that 11.g3 might of been better.
Expected.
Maybe 12Bf3+ was not so much a good move here, maybe 12.Be6 may of been better.
Black moves his king out of check.
Trying to develop my bishop on c1.

Here I am preparing to castle on queen side and stop blacks knight from landing on b4.
Expected.
Moving my knight here will protect the c2 square from blacks knight. But after blacks next move I realised that this was a bad move.
I should have moved 15.Bfd1 as now I have lost my bishop on f3 to blacks knight and I am in check.
